Helper functions to visualize intermarriage rates. The first draws two lines, one for observed and one for adjusted, and has optional arguments to group by a variable (e.g.Â \(\texttt{Province}\)), and exclude the low power decades of 1921-1930 and 1931-1940. The second computes the difference and plots it. Both draw 95% confidence intervals.

plot_intermarriage <- function(data, title, group_var = NULL, exclude_decade = TRUE) {
    names(data) <- gsub("National_", "", names(data))
    names(data) <- gsub("Province_", "", names(data))
    names(data) <- gsub("Const_", "", names(data))

    if (exclude_decade) {
        data <- data %>% filter(!DecadeMarried %in% c("1921-1930", "1931-1940", "1941-1950"))
    }
    
    if (!is.null(group_var)) {
        data <- data %>% mutate(group = .data[[group_var]])
    } else {
        data <- data %>% mutate(group = 1)
    }
    
    data <- data %>%
        mutate(
            Observed_CI_lower = Observed_mean - 1.96 * Observed_SE,
            Observed_CI_upper = Observed_mean + 1.96 * Observed_SE,
            Adjusted_CI_lower = Adjusted_mean - 1.96 * Adjusted_SE,
            Adjusted_CI_upper = Adjusted_mean + 1.96 * Adjusted_SE,
            Expectation_CI_lower = Expectation_mean - 1.96 * Expectation_SE,
            Expectation_CI_upper = Expectation_mean + 1.96 * Expectation_SE
        )
    
    ggplot(data) +
    geom_line(aes(x = DecadeMarried, y = Observed_mean, group = group, color = "Observed")) +
    geom_ribbon(aes(x = DecadeMarried, ymin = Observed_CI_lower, ymax = Observed_CI_upper, group = group, fill = "Observed"), alpha = 0.1) +
    geom_line(aes(x = DecadeMarried, y = Adjusted_mean, group = group, color = "Controlling for Exposure")) +
    geom_ribbon(aes(x = DecadeMarried, ymin = Adjusted_CI_lower, ymax = Adjusted_CI_upper, group = group, fill = "Controlling for Exposure"), alpha = 0.1) +
    geom_line(aes(x = DecadeMarried, y = Expectation_mean, group = group, color = "Expected")) +
    geom_ribbon(aes(x = DecadeMarried, ymin = Expectation_CI_lower, ymax = Expectation_CI_upper, group = group, fill = "Expected"), alpha = 0.1) +
    scale_color_manual(values = c("Observed" = "red", "Controlling for Exposure" = "blue", "Expected" = "black")) +
    scale_fill_manual(values = c("Observed" = "red", "Controlling for Exposure" = "blue", "Expected" = "black"), guide = "none") +
    theme_pubclean() +
    theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, vjust = 1, hjust = 1)) +
    labs(title = title, color = "", fill = "", x = "Decade Married", y = "Value")

}

plot_intermarriage_difference <- function(data, title, group_var = NULL, exclude_decade = TRUE) {
    names(data) <- gsub("National_", "", names(data))
    names(data) <- gsub("Province_", "", names(data))
    names(data) <- gsub("Const_", "", names(data))

    if (exclude_decade) {
        data <- data %>% filter(!DecadeMarried %in% c("1921-1930", "1931-1940", "1941-1950"))
    }
    
    if (!is.null(group_var)) {
        data <- data %>% mutate(group = .data[[group_var]])
    } else {
        data <- data %>% mutate(group = 1)
    }
    
    data <- data %>%
        mutate(
            Difference = Adjusted_mean - Observed_mean,
            Difference_SE = sqrt(Adjusted_SE^2 + Observed_SE^2),
            CI_lower = Difference - 1.96 * Difference_SE,
            CI_upper = Difference + 1.96 * Difference_SE
        )
    
    ggplot(data) +
        geom_line(aes(x = DecadeMarried, y = Difference, group = group, color = as.factor(group))) +
        geom_ribbon(aes(x = DecadeMarried, ymin = CI_lower, ymax = CI_upper, group = group, fill = as.factor(group)), alpha = 0.1) +
        scale_color_discrete(name = group_var) +
        scale_fill_discrete(name = group_var) +
        theme_pubclean() +
        theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, vjust = 1, hjust = 1)) +
        labs(title = title, color = "", x = "Decade Married", y = "Difference (Controlling for Exposure - Observed)")
}

Weighted standard errors that account for effective degrees of freedom:

weighted_se_mean <- function(x, w, na.rm = TRUE) {
    if (na.rm) {
        i <- !is.na(x)
        w <- w[i]
        x <- x[i]
    }
    n_eff <- (sum(w))^2 / sum(w^2)
    correction <- n_eff / (n_eff - 1)
    numerator <- sum(w * (x - weighted.mean(x, w))^2)
    denominator <- sum(w)
    sqrt((correction * (numerator / denominator)) / n_eff)
}

Process constituency-level data, storing the observed, expected, and adjusted values. Also finds the population with the number of rows. Process is repeated for ethnic blocks. NAs are removed because some denominators are zero (aka no exposure due to small samples) â all data has been scanned for missingness.

process_constituency_ethnic <- function(data) {
    const_intermarriage_ethnic <- data %>%
        select(Const, District, Province, Ethnicity, EthnicOutmarriage) %>%
        left_join(y = ethnic_proportions, by = join_by(Const, Ethnicity)) %>%
        group_by(Const, District, Province, Ethnicity, Proportion) %>%
        reframe(Observed = mean(EthnicOutmarriage), n = n()) %>%
        mutate(Expectation = 1 - Proportion) %>%
        mutate(Adjusted = Observed / Expectation) %>%
        ungroup()

    const_ethnic <- const_intermarriage_ethnic %>%
        group_by(Const, District, Province) %>%
        mutate(Const_Population = sum(n)) %>%
        ungroup()

    const_ethnic <- const_ethnic %>%
        group_by(Const, District, Province) %>%
        summarise(
            Const_Population = sum(n),
            Const_Adjusted_mean = weighted.mean(Adjusted, Proportion, na.rm = TRUE),
            Const_Observed_mean = weighted.mean(Observed, Proportion, na.rm = TRUE),
            Const_Expectation_mean = weighted.mean(Expectation, Proportion, na.rm = TRUE),
            Adjusted_SE = weighted_se_mean(Adjusted, Proportion),
            Observed_SE = weighted_se_mean(Observed, Proportion),
            Expectation_SE = weighted_se_mean(Expectation, Proportion)
        ) %>%
        ungroup() %>%
        left_join(y = const_hhi, join_by(Const))

    #print("Processed constituencies")
    return(const_ethnic)
}

process_constituency_block <- function(data) {
    const_intermarriage_block <- data %>%
        select(Const, District, Province, EthnicBlock, BlockOutmarriage) %>%
        left_join(y = ethnic_block_proportions, by = join_by(Const, EthnicBlock)) %>%
        group_by(Const, District, Province, EthnicBlock, Proportion) %>%
        reframe(Observed = mean(BlockOutmarriage), n = n()) %>%
        mutate(Expectation = 1 - Proportion) %>%
        mutate(Adjusted = Observed / Expectation) %>%
        ungroup()

    const_block <- const_intermarriage_block %>%
        group_by(Const, District, Province) %>%
        mutate(Const_Population = sum(n)) %>%
        ungroup()

    const_block <- const_block %>%
        group_by(Const, District, Province) %>%
        summarise(
            Const_Population = sum(n),
            Const_Adjusted_mean = weighted.mean(Adjusted, Proportion, na.rm = TRUE),
            Const_Observed_mean = weighted.mean(Observed, Proportion, na.rm = TRUE),
            Const_Expectation_mean = weighted.mean(Expectation, Proportion, na.rm = TRUE),
            Adjusted_SE = weighted_se_mean(Adjusted, Proportion),
            Observed_SE = weighted_se_mean(Observed, Proportion),
            Expectation_SE = weighted_se_mean(Expectation, Proportion)
        ) %>%
        ungroup() %>%
        left_join(y = const_hhi, join_by(Const))

    return(const_block)
    #"Processed constituencies, ethnic block")
}

Aggregate from constituencies to provinces. We weigh both the means and the standard errors by population. Process is repeated for the countrywide estimates.

aggregate_to_district <- function(const_data) {
    district_data <- const_data %>%
    select(-Const) %>%
    group_by(District) %>%
    summarise(
        District_Population = sum(Const_Population),
        District_Adjusted_mean = weighted.mean(Const_Adjusted_mean, Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE),
        District_Observed_mean = weighted.mean(Const_Observed_mean, Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE),
        District_Expectation_mean = weighted.mean(Const_Expectation_mean, Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE),
        District_Adjusted_SE = weighted_se_mean(Const_Adjusted_mean, Const_Population),
        District_Observed_SE = weighted_se_mean(Const_Observed_mean, Const_Population),
        District_Expectation_SE = weighted_se_mean(Const_Expectation_mean, Const_Population),
        District_HHI = weighted.mean(hhi, Const_Population)
    ) %>%
    ungroup()
    #print("Processed districts")
    return(district_data)
}

aggregate_to_province <- function(const_data) {
    province_data <- const_data %>%
    select(-Const, -District) %>%
    group_by(Province) %>%
    summarise(
        Province_Population = sum(Const_Population),
        Province_Adjusted_mean = weighted.mean(Const_Adjusted_mean, Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE),
        Province_Observed_mean = weighted.mean(Const_Observed_mean, Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE),
        Province_Expectation_mean = weighted.mean(Const_Expectation_mean, Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE),
        Province_Adjusted_SE = weighted_se_mean(Const_Adjusted_mean, Const_Population),
        Province_Observed_SE = weighted_se_mean(Const_Observed_mean, Const_Population),
        Province_Expectation_SE = weighted_se_mean(Const_Expectation_mean, Const_Population),
        Province_HHI = weighted.mean(hhi, Const_Population)
    ) %>%
    ungroup()
    #print("Processed provinces")
    return(province_data)
}

aggregate_to_national <- function(const_data) {
    national_data <- const_data %>%
    select(-Const, -District, -Province) %>%
    summarise(
        National_Population = sum(Const_Population),
        National_Adjusted_mean = weighted.mean(Const_Adjusted_mean, Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE),
        National_Observed_mean = weighted.mean(Const_Observed_mean, Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE),
        National_Expectation_mean = weighted.mean(Const_Expectation_mean, Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE),
        National_Adjusted_SE = weighted_se_mean(Const_Adjusted_mean, Const_Population),
        National_Observed_SE = weighted_se_mean(Const_Observed_mean, Const_Population),
        National_Expectation_SE = weighted_se_mean(Const_Expectation_mean, Const_Population),
        National_HHI = weighted.mean(hhi, Const_Population)
    ) %>%
    ungroup()

    #print("Processed national")
    return(national_data)
}

Connect functions together.

calculate_results <- function(data) {
    const_ethnic <- process_constituency_ethnic(data)
    const_block <- process_constituency_block(data)
    
    provincial_ethnic <- aggregate_to_province(const_ethnic)
    provincial_block <- aggregate_to_province(const_block)
    
    national_ethnic <- aggregate_to_national(const_ethnic)
    national_block <- aggregate_to_national(const_block)

    const_ethnic_by_decade <- process_constituency_ethnic_by_decade(data)
    const_block_by_decade <- process_constituency_block_by_decade(data)

    national_ethnic_by_decade <- aggregate_to_national_by_decade(const_ethnic_by_decade)
    national_block_by_decade <- aggregate_to_national_by_decade(const_block_by_decade)

    list(
        const_ethnic = const_ethnic,
        const_block = const_block,
        national_ethnic = national_ethnic,
        national_block = national_block,
        province_ethnic = provincial_ethnic,
        province_block = provincial_block,
        national_ethnic_by_decade = national_ethnic_by_decade,
        national_block_by_decade = national_block_by_decade
    )
}

Run iterations of the function for every sample we are interested in.

run_filters <- function(data) {
    filters <- list(
        "full" = data,
        "urban" = data %>% filter(Urbanization >= 0.5),
        "urban_quart" = data %>% filter(Urbanization >= 0.75),
        "rural" = data %>% filter(Urbanization < 0.5),
        "rural_quart" = data %>% filter(Urbanization <= 0.25)
    )
    
    results_dfs <- list()

    for (filter_name in names(filters)) {
        filtered_data <- filters[[filter_name]]
        result <- calculate_results(filtered_data)
        
        results_dfs[[paste0(filter_name, "_const_ethnic")]] <- result$const_ethnic
        results_dfs[[paste0(filter_name, "_const_block")]] <- result$const_block
        results_dfs[[paste0(filter_name, "_national_ethnic")]] <- result$national_ethnic
        results_dfs[[paste0(filter_name, "_national_block")]] <- result$national_block
        results_dfs[[paste0(filter_name, "_province_ethnic")]] <- result$province_ethnic
        results_dfs[[paste0(filter_name, "_province_block")]] <- result$province_block
        results_dfs[[paste0(filter_name, "_national_ethnic_by_decade")]] <- result$national_ethnic_by_decade
        results_dfs[[paste0(filter_name, "_national_block_by_decade")]] <- result$national_block_by_decade
    }
    
    results_dfs
}

all_results_dfs <- run_filters(individuals)

Plots by urbanization group.

process_constituency_ethnic_by_urbanization <- function(data) {
    const_intermarriage_ethnic <- data %>%
        mutate(Urbanization_Group = cut(Urbanization, breaks = seq(0, 1, by = 0.1), labels = seq(0.1, 1, by = 0.1), include.lowest = TRUE)) %>%
        select(Const, District, Province, Ethnicity, EthnicOutmarriage, Urbanization_Group) %>%
        left_join(y = ethnic_proportions, by = join_by(Const, Ethnicity)) %>%
        group_by(Const, District, Province, Ethnicity, Proportion, Urbanization_Group) %>%
        reframe(Observed = mean(EthnicOutmarriage), n = n()) %>%
        mutate(Expectation = 1 - Proportion) %>%
        mutate(Adjusted = Observed / Expectation) %>%
        ungroup()

    const_ethnic <- const_intermarriage_ethnic %>%
        group_by(Const, District, Province, Urbanization_Group) %>%
        summarise(
            Const_Population = sum(n),
            Const_Adjusted_mean = weighted.mean(Adjusted, Proportion, na.rm = TRUE),
            Const_Observed_mean = weighted.mean(Observed, Proportion, na.rm = TRUE),
            Const_Expectation_mean = weighted.mean(Expectation, Proportion, na.rm = TRUE),
            Adjusted_SE = weighted_se_mean(Adjusted, Proportion),
            Observed_SE = weighted_se_mean(Observed, Proportion),
            Expectation_SE = weighted_se_mean(Expectation, Proportion)
        ) %>%
        ungroup()

    urbanization_ethnic <- const_ethnic %>%
        group_by(Urbanization_Group) %>%
        summarise(
            Urbanization_Population = sum(Const_Population),
            Urbanization_Adjusted_mean = weighted.mean(Const_Adjusted_mean, Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE),
            Urbanization_Observed_mean = weighted.mean(Const_Observed_mean, Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE),
            Urbanization_Expectation_mean = weighted.mean(Const_Expectation_mean, Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE),
            Adjusted_SE = weighted_se_mean(Const_Adjusted_mean, Const_Population),
            Observed_SE = weighted_se_mean(Const_Observed_mean, Const_Population),
            Expectation_SE = weighted_se_mean(Const_Expectation_mean, Const_Population)
        ) %>%
        mutate(
            Adjusted_CI_lower = Urbanization_Adjusted_mean - 1.96 * Adjusted_SE,
            Adjusted_CI_upper = Urbanization_Adjusted_mean + 1.96 * Adjusted_SE,
            Observed_CI_lower = Urbanization_Observed_mean - 1.96 * Observed_SE,
            Observed_CI_upper = Urbanization_Observed_mean + 1.96 * Observed_SE,
            Expectation_CI_lower = Urbanization_Expectation_mean - 1.96 * Expectation_SE,
            Expectation_CI_upper = Urbanization_Expectation_mean + 1.96 * Expectation_SE
        ) %>%
        ungroup()

    return(urbanization_ethnic)
}

process_constituency_block_by_urbanization <- function(data) {
    const_intermarriage_block <- data %>%
        mutate(Urbanization_Group = cut(Urbanization, breaks = seq(0, 1, by = 0.1), labels = seq(0.1, 1, by = 0.1), include.lowest = TRUE)) %>%
        select(Const, District, Province, EthnicBlock, BlockOutmarriage, Urbanization_Group) %>%
        left_join(y = ethnic_block_proportions, by = join_by(Const, EthnicBlock)) %>%
        group_by(Const, District, Province, EthnicBlock, Proportion, Urbanization_Group) %>%
        reframe(Observed = mean(BlockOutmarriage), n = n()) %>%
        mutate(Expectation = 1 - Proportion) %>%
        mutate(Adjusted = Observed / Expectation) %>%
        ungroup()

    const_block <- const_intermarriage_block %>%
        group_by(Const, District, Province, Urbanization_Group) %>%
        summarise(
            Const_Population = sum(n),
            Const_Adjusted_mean = weighted.mean(Adjusted, Proportion, na.rm = TRUE),
            Const_Observed_mean = weighted.mean(Observed, Proportion, na.rm = TRUE),
            Const_Expectation_mean = weighted.mean(Expectation, Proportion, na.rm = TRUE),
            Adjusted_SE = weighted_se_mean(Adjusted, Proportion),
            Observed_SE = weighted_se_mean(Observed, Proportion),
            Expectation_SE = weighted_se_mean(Expectation, Proportion)
        ) %>%
        ungroup()

    urbanization_block <- const_block %>%
        group_by(Urbanization_Group) %>%
        summarise(
            Urbanization_Population = sum(Const_Population),
            Urbanization_Adjusted_mean = weighted.mean(Const_Adjusted_mean, Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE),
            Urbanization_Observed_mean = weighted.mean(Const_Observed_mean, Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE),
            Urbanization_Expectation_mean = weighted.mean(Const_Expectation_mean, Const_Population, na.rm = TRUE),
            Adjusted_SE = weighted_se_mean(Const_Adjusted_mean, Const_Population),
            Observed_SE = weighted_se_mean(Const_Observed_mean, Const_Population),
            Expectation_SE = weighted_se_mean(Const_Expectation_mean, Const_Population)
        ) %>%
        mutate(
            Adjusted_CI_lower = Urbanization_Adjusted_mean - 1.96 * Adjusted_SE,
            Adjusted_CI_upper = Urbanization_Adjusted_mean + 1.96 * Adjusted_SE,
            Observed_CI_lower = Urbanization_Observed_mean - 1.96 * Observed_SE,
            Observed_CI_upper = Urbanization_Observed_mean + 1.96 * Observed_SE,
            Expectation_CI_lower = Urbanization_Expectation_mean - 1.96 * Expectation_SE,
            Expectation_CI_upper = Urbanization_Expectation_mean + 1.96 * Expectation_SE
        ) %>%
        ungroup()

    return(urbanization_block)
}
